<h1 class="title">Naive Limit Combination</h1>
<p>
When combining limits from two different measurements, the naive combination &#x2013; which assumes the measurements are completely independent is given by
</p>


<p>
\[
\sigma_c = \sqrt{\frac{1}{\frac{1}{\sigma_1^2} + \frac{1}{\sigma_2^2}}} = \frac{\sigma_1\sigma_2}{\sqrt{\sigma_1^2+\sigma_2^2}}
\] 
</p>


<p>
If \(\sigma_1=\sigma_2\), 
\[
\sigma_c = \frac{\sigma^2}{\sqrt{2\sigma}} = \frac{\sigma}{\sqrt{2}}
\]
</p>




